! Organoid Lambda Calibration

Concrete calibration finding from the compression lane: `LAMBDA_B = 0.08` was
structurally too weak to affect compression selection, while `0.50` was proposed
from break-even analysis. The same thread links organoid three-state behavior to
K=3 encoding and identifies ROT_R recalibration as a measurement gap.

